Next he assails Sthenius, and Anchemolus of Rhoetus' ancient line, who dared defile his stepdame's bed. Ye too, twin brethren, fell on Rutulian plains‚ Larides and Thymber, sons of Daueus, most like in semblance, indistinguishable to kindred, and to their own parents a sweet perplexity. But a grim difference now has Pallas made between you. For thy head, Thymber, had Evander’s sword swept off; while thy severed hand, Larides, seeks its master, and the dying fingers twitch and clutch again at the sword.
